sharedPost.text:
By legend polskiego kina i ulubiecem najmodszych widz贸w. Prywatnie Mieczysaw Czechowicz nosi w sobie tajemnic, o kt贸rej milcza cae 偶ycie

Polacy znaj go z filmu Poszukiwany, poszukiwana, z roli profesora zajtego rzekomo naukowymi badaniami oraz z gosu Misia Uszatka, kt贸ry przez lata towarzyszy dzieciom przed telewizorami. Mieczysaw Czechowicz by jedn z tych postaci, kt贸re wydaway si zawsze ciepe, pogodne i bezpieczne. Wybitny aktor komediowy, legenda kina i teatru, czowiek obdarzony niezwykym talentem i charakterystycznym gosem. Niewielu jednak wiedziao, 偶e za t pogod kryo si dowiadczenie, kt贸re na zawsze go uksztatowao i o kt贸rym niemal nigdy nie m贸wi.
Urodzi si w 1930 roku w Lublinie, dziecistwo spdzi na Kresach. Wojna odebraa mu poczucie bezpieczestwa bardzo wczenie. Ojciec trafi do niewoli, rodzina zostaa zmuszona do cigych zmian miejsca zamieszkania, a g贸d i strach zapisay si w jego pamici na cae 偶ycie. Ju偶 jako dorosy czowiek, znany i ceniony aktor, nosi w sobie lk przed bied. Raz w miesicu robi sobie dzie, w kt贸rym jad bez ogranicze, jakby chcia nadrobi wszystko to, czego zabrako w dziecistwie.
Jako bardzo mody chopak zaanga偶owa si w dziaalno konspiracyjn. Zapaci za to wysok cen. Zosta aresztowany, przeszed ci偶kie dowiadczenia, kt贸re odcisny pitno na jego zdrowiu i psychice. Cho by postawnym, silnym m偶czyzn, przez cae 偶ycie zmaga si z problemami zdrowotnymi, szczeg贸lnie z sercem. Tych lat nie wspomina. To bya jego tajemnica, noszona w ciszy i zamknita gboko w sobie.
Aktorstwo byo jego marzeniem i ucieczk zarazem. Ukoczy szko teatraln w Warszawie i bardzo szybko zosta zauwa偶ony. Krytycy pisali o jego niezwykej vis comica, naturalnym humorze, scenicznej prawdzie i ogromnej sympatii, jak budzi w widzach. Gra w teatrze, filmie i kabarecie. By ulubiecem Stanisawa Barei, byszcza w Kabarecie Starszych Pan贸w, tworzy role, kt贸re do dzi s pamitane i cytowane. Jednoczenie pozosta skromny i kole偶eski, zawsze bliski ludziom.
Prywatnie by czowiekiem zamknitym. O偶eni si z Eugeni liwisk, z kt贸r spdzi cae 偶ycie. Cho po latach prze偶y jeszcze jedn, bardzo trudn mio, nie zdecydowa si na odejcie. Kierowa si lojalnoci i szacunkiem, nawet kosztem wasnego szczcia. To r贸wnie偶 byo co, o czym nie m贸wi gono. Emocje tumi w sobie, co odbijao si na jego zdrowiu.
Zmar w 1991 roku, zbyt wczenie, pozostawiajc po sobie role, gos i wspomnienie czowieka dobrego, ciepego i niezwykle utalentowanego. Mieczysaw Czechowicz mieszy miliony, dawa dzieciom poczucie spokoju, a dorosym chwile wytchnienia. Sam jednak przez cae 偶ycie ni贸s w sobie ci偶ar przeszoci, o kt贸rym wiedzieli nieliczni. I mo偶e wanie dlatego jego umiech na ekranie by tak prawdziwy.
__
 fot. BOLESAW MIEDZA/PAP

I wanted to share my gratitude for what was an outstanding holiday season of events, ranging from the local Midas Sign that kick things off this season  to the tree lighting ceremony at the Capitol in Sacramento.

Thank you to the University of California Student and Policy Center for the invitation to their well-stocked reception. The conversation was marvelousI haven't laughed that hard or had such deep conversations that left me wanting more in a long time. I also appreciate the Berkeley Policy Center for their intriguing night of discussion.

Finally, a shout-out to my friends at Sacramento Startup for the fun night at the Urban Hive. It is truly shaping up to be the place for events and gatherings, and I look forward to hosting an event there soon.

Start the new year learning, networking and making movies!.

Free introductory cinematography and direction workshop Saturday January 3rd, 2026. In Los Angeles

Complete this form for your free workshop https://forms.gle/hbAKhwT4jTsXzofXA

**Unlock Your Filmmaking Potential:**

 Step onto a professional film set, gaining real-world experience while receiving guidance from seasoned instructors who are committed to your success. Be part of a film crew and make movies!

 Immerse yourself in a vibrant and supportive community that empowers filmmakers to build connections and elevate their careers. Make friends for life.

 Dive into hands-on workshops with cutting-edge digital cinema cameras and lighting equipment, bringing your creative vision to life like never before.

 Gain exclusive access to our state-of-the-art studio, along with multiple stunning filming locations that will transform your projects into visual masterpieces.

 Take advantage of free networking events featuring industry luminaries, where youll have the chance to meet fellow filmmakers and gain invaluable insights.

 Learn from industry veterans as they visit our studio, providing exclusive training sessions and mentorship opportunities that can shape your future in film.

 Complete our intensive courses and earn a completion certificate that showcases your dedication and skills.

info@empoweringfilmmakers.org

items.text:
## CASTING CALL  AMBER (LEAD rOLE)

**Project: Short Film**

Genre: Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller

Shoot Location: Lower Mainland, BC

Shoot Dates: TBD

Compensation: Volunteer / Passion Project

**ROLE: AMBER**

Age Range: 2740

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Open / Race-agnostic

**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chasealways moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she relies on it too much. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern lifenot in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.

**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a subtle, internal performance. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Ambers collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettlingdriven by over-certainty and loss of trust in her own judgment.

**KEY TRAITS**

Intelligent

Controlled

Ambitious (not arrogant)

Emotionally guarded

Increasingly detached

**AUDITION REQUIREMENTS**

Self-tape audition

One dramatic scene (sides to be provided)

**SUBMISSION DETAILS**

Please submit:

Headshot

Resume (if available)

Email submissions to: soultales.ca@gmail.com

Subject: AMBER  Casting Submission

**NOTE!!!**

This is a serious passion project with a small, committed team. We are looking for actors who are reliable, prepared, and respectful of time and effort. Please apply only if you can fully commit to rehearsals, shoot days, and clear communication throughout the process. Consistency and follow-through are essential for this role.

This project is not suitable for flaky or tentative participation. If you are unsure about your availability or commitment, we kindly ask that you do not apply.

items.text:
Stanislavski vs Meisner - Which Technique Is Right for You?

Every actor eventually asks this question:
**Do I build from the inside outor live in the moment?**

Stanislavski and Meisner are two of the most influential acting techniques ever createdbut they train very different muscles.

One focuses on *inner truth.*
The other on *real-time reaction.*

Understanding the difference can change your entire approach to acting.

 Learn the full breakdown at **cineconnectstagecraft.org**

What Casting Directors Are Actually Looking For

Actors often think auditions are about impressing. Casting Directors are actually looking for clarity, professionalism, and trust.
Every audition silently answers three questions:
Can you do the role?
Can you take direction?
Can we work with you?
When you understand that, your auditions change completely.
 Read the full guide:
 https://cineconnectstagecraft.org

What Casting Directors Are Actually Looking For Auditions arent about impressing  theyre about trust.

Casting Directors are quietly asking:
 Can you do the role?
 Can you take direction?
 Can we work with you?

When you understand that, your auditions change.

 [https://cineconnectstagecraft.org](https://cineconnectstagecraft.org/)

**RUSH CALL!**

**Are you a LARPer, reenactor, or HEMA fighter who already owns armor and just wants to swing a sword on camera?**

Narrowcast Productions and Good Fruit Media are putting together a **rush medieval battle shoot** for a low-budget, proof-of-concept short film titled ***To the Hilt***, and were looking for **knights and foot soldiers** to fill the frame.

**When? January 5****th**** in the afternoon/evening**
**Where? Just north of Bellville, TX (more details upon email)**
**Commitment?** **Approx. 2.53 hours**

**THE DEAL:**

路 Background warriors (no speaking roles)

路 Possible featured extras

路 Swordplay only

路 Non-union

路 **Unpaid passion project** (meal provided *after* the shoot)

**YOU MUST:**

路 Be a male legal adult (18-50s)

路 Bring your **own medieval wardrobe/armor** (1000-1200s-era look)

路 Arrive costume ready. This shoot will move fast.

路 Have safe weapons (props preferred, but bring what you can)

**EXPERIENCE:**
Stage combat, reenactment, Buhurt, HEMA, or SCA experience preferred  but if you can fight with a broadsword convincingly, well take it.

**IMPORTANT: **

路 Choreography will be mostly **self-determined** (no pre-rehearsal time)

路 We are not liable for any injuries or damaged equipment. Act accordingly.

路 Some performers may do paired combat

路 Due to location limits, we can only take **18 people max**

 **To submit:**
Send headshot, armor photos, experience (if any), IMDb (optional), and questions to
**narrowcastproductions@gmail.com**

If youve ever wanted to look like you stepped out of a medieval chronicle for an afternoon  this is your shot.

ISO a female lead actress (ages 2228) for an upcoming 

independent short film titled The Monster.

Location: Downtown Grand Rapids, Michigan

Shoot: Night shoots, Friday & Saturday nights (dates TBD)

Type: Non-union / Unpaid

The film has two lead characters; the male lead is already cast. Im looking for the female lead for this project.

Requirements:

Comfortable with night shoots

Able to put together your own outfit

Able to do your own hair & makeup

This will be my second short film (the first one is almost ready to be shared). The concept will be discussed privately.

If interested, please message me to:

Confirm availability for Friday & Saturday nights

Confirm comfort with wardrobe, hair, and makeup

Well then set up a quick Zoom call to discuss the role and details.

Thank you in advance . 

You can see my work on Instagram 

www.instagram.com/syed_ali_raza_usama

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

Cze,
Jestemy agencj marketingow  **Contenty.pl**, specjalizujc si przede wszystkim w tworzeniu TikTok贸w dla firm.

Szukamy **aktorki**, kt贸ra bdzie dla nas nagrywa kr贸tkie materiay wideo (TikToki/Reelsy) dla marki z bran偶y farmaceutycznej 

Nagrania odbywaj si **stacjonarnie w naszym biurze w Krakowie przy ul. Emaus**.
Cao potrwa **maksymalnie 4 godziny**.

***Co trzeba umie?***
* Naturalnie wypa przed kamer.
* Pynnie wypowiedzie kr贸tkie kwestie, wedug scenariusza.
* Odda emocje zgodnie z wytycznymi (umiech, lekkie zdziwienie, aha moment itp.).
* By dyspozycyjn w Krakowie na nagrania (ok. 4h).

Nie wymagamy dowiadczenia aktorskiego  **wystarczy, 偶e dobrze czujesz si przed kamer i masz naturalny vibe**.

***Wynagrodzenie***

Rozliczamy si **per filmik**.
Pacimy **50 z brutto za nagranie jednego TikToka**.
cznie do nagrania jest **12 filmik贸w = 600 z brutto**.

Forma wsp贸pracy: **Umowa Zlecenie**.

***Jak wyglda proces wsp贸pracy?***

Nasza Koordynatorka skontaktuje si z Tob - na maila dostaniesz od nas scenariusze oraz wskaz贸wki, czego bdziemy oczekiwali na nagraniach. Podpiszemy umow zlecenie, a nastpnie spotykamy si w naszym biurze w Krakowie. Nagrywamy wszystkie materiay jednego dnia (ok. 4h).
Po nagraniach  temat zamknity, a my przejmujemy ca reszt (monta偶, poprawki, wysyki do klienta).

***Proces rekrutacji***

Wypenij formularz rekrutacyjny:

W formularzu poprosimy Ci o:
* imi i nazwisko
* mail
* numer telefonu
* **portfolio / pr贸bki video** (np. linki do TikTok贸w, Reels贸w, film贸w, materia贸w nagranych telefonem)

Najciekawszym osobom damy zna i zaprosimy do kolejnego etapu

Rozliczamy si **per filmik**.
Pacimy **50 z brutto za nagranie jednego TikToka**.
cznie do nagrania jest **12 filmik贸w = 600 z brutto**.

Forma wsp贸pracy: **Umowa Zlecenie**.

***Jak wyglda proces wsp贸pracy?***

Nasza Koordynatorka skontaktuje si z Tob - na maila dostaniesz od nas scenariusze oraz wskaz贸wki, czego bdziemy oczekiwali na nagraniach. Podpiszemy umow zlecenie, a nastpnie spotykamy si w naszym biurze w Krakowie. Nagrywamy wszystkie materiay jednego dnia (ok. 4h).
Po nagraniach  temat zamknity, a my przejmujemy ca reszt (monta偶, poprawki, wysyki do klienta).

***Proces rekrutacji***

Wypenij formularz rekrutacyjny:
 https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScNClfSvNg3IC7oOdx0IK_MEzybHXcQJluU_QZT3-cGBpFg9A/viewform?usp=sharing&ouid=101087389624265887840

W formularzu poprosimy Ci o:
* imi i nazwisko
* mail
* numer telefonu
* **portfolio / pr贸bki video** (np. linki do TikTok贸w, Reels贸w, film贸w, materia贸w nagranych telefonem)

Najciekawszym osobom damy zna i zaprosimy do kolejnego etapu

CASTING CALL  SHORT FILM (UK) 

Title: INTELLIGENCE UNLEASHED
Genre: Thriller / Crime / Revenge
Shoot Location: UK (North England  Manchester area preferred)
Shoot Dates: TBC (Approx. 4 days)
Format: Short Film (Festival-focused)

Paid: No.
Scene showreel footage provided. Opportunity for international festival exposure and visibility to film academies.
 If any cast member wins Best Actor at a festival, 拢700 will be awarded by the production.

We are casting for an intense, character-driven short film exploring grief, intelligence, crime, and revenge. We are looking for committed actors comfortable with emotionally demanding material.

 ROLES AVAILABLE
ETHAN CROSS (1820)  MALE

Lead Role

A brilliant, introverted young programmer whose life is shattered by his fathers murder. Emotionally layered: grief, restraint, intelligence, and controlled rage. Must convincingly play quiet intensity and emotional transitions.

Key traits: Intelligent, reserved, emotionally deep, dangerous when pushed
Scenes include: Emotional drama, intense solo moments
Accent: Any neutral UK accent

THERON CROSS (40s)  MALE

Supporting Role

Ethans father. A loving family man hiding a dangerous past. Warm, protective, conflicted. Appears in family scenes and flashbacks.

Key traits: Charismatic, protective, morally conflicted
Scenes include: Family drama, crime confrontation

EVELYN CROSS (40s)  FEMALE

Supporting Role

Ethans mother. Strong, loving, emotionally shattered by loss. Must handle raw grief and intimate emotional scenes.

Key traits: Warm, resilient, emotionally powerful
Scenes include: Grief, emotional dialogue

GORGOS (Late 40s50s)  MALE

Antagonist

Cold, intelligent criminal mastermind. Calm, intimidating, and charismatic. Believes in control, loyalty, and eliminating loose ends.

Key traits: Menacing calm, authority, intelligence
Scenes include: Threatening dialogue, criminal negotiations
Accent: Open (UK / European welcome)

THE ASSASSIN (30s40s)  MALE

Supporting Role

Professional hitman. Silent, controlled, predatory. Minimal dialogue but strong physical presence required.

Key traits: Intimidating, disciplined, physical confidence
Scenes include: Weapon handling (prop only), intense confrontation
 No real firearms used

GORGOS RIGHT-HAND MAN (30s40s)  MALE

Small Supporting Role

Loyal enforcer. Observant, calculating, dangerous.

 IMPORTANT NOTES

All weapons are prop / air guns only

Professional insurance & safety protocols in place

Suitable for actors building strong showreel material

IMDb credit provided

 TO APPLY

Please send:

Name

Age

Location

Headshot

Showreel (if available)

 Subject: INTELLIGENCE UNLEASHED  Role
To  Email:  roxanne.marie51119@gmail.com

items.text:
We are casting for an updated tour of the childrens theatre show, The Dinosaur That Pooped a Rock Show, based on the popular books by McFlys Tom Fletcher and Dougie Poynter. 

The show is written and directed by Miranda Larson with songs and music by Tom Fletcher & Dougie Poynter and Barrie Bignold and is produced by Mark Thompson at MT Productions. 

**Production dates:**

Auditions will take place on 24th November 2025

Rehearsals begin on 12th January  22nd January 2026 in London
Tour dates Jan  Nov 2026.
We are currently have 91 dates and counting. 

**Production location: **Greater London

**Role: **We are looking for a costume character/ skin artist to play the role of Dino. The artist will need to operate Dinos mouth, hands and head, bringing the character to life. They will also be required to join in dance moves and routines whilst inside the costume. We are looking for someone between 56 and 510 tall. Previous skin/ costume character experience is essential.

The successful applicant will need to have a full UK drivers licence and will be comfortable driving the touring van on a shared basis with the rest of the company.

Please send CV's & headshots to: casting.mtproductions@gmail.com

**Fees:**

Rehearsal fee: 拢550pw

Show day fee: 拢150

Travel day fee: 拢50

Subsistence: 拢20

items.text:
Jestem freelancerem z okiem filmowca.

Tworz spersonalizowane, ULTRA REALISTYCZNE filmy wideo AI z TOB w roli g贸wnej  dla Ciebie, Twoich usug, Twojej marki albo Twojego klienta.

Ja nie robi adnych rolek.
Ja robi FILM.

Hiperrealistyka, filmowe kadry, filmowe wiato, filmowy monta偶.
Ujcia, kt贸re wygldaj jak ze studia  nie jak z aplikacji.

I tak: chodzi o JAKO.
O detale.
O twarz.
O sk贸r.
O mikrodetal.

Jeli chcesz materia wow  taki, 偶e ludzie patrz i maj w gowie: co to jest, jak to jest zrobione? 
to jest dokadnie to.


CO MO呕ESZ DOSTA 


Zastosowania s pot偶ne i szerokie:
 reklama produkt贸w
 reklama Ciebie jako freelancera / marki osobistej
 showcase usugi
 teaser / trailer projektu
 sceny, kt贸rych jeszcze nie krcie (bo nie masz planu, lokacji, aktor贸w)

Mo偶esz by wasnym modelem swojej marki.
Mo偶esz prezentowa ubrania, kosmetyki.
Mo偶esz chodzi po wybiegu.
Mo偶esz jecha samochodem.
Mo偶esz siedzie w restauracji.
Mo偶esz by na koncercie.

A film bdzie przepeniony ujciami pokazujcymi:
Ciebie, Twoj twarz, Twoje emocje, Twoje otoczenie.

W jakoci HYPERREAL.
Z detalem sk贸ry.
Z faktur.
Z mikro woskiem.
Z ka偶dym pieprzykiem.




Pracuj tylko i wycznie zdalnie.

Nie potrzebuj studia.
Nie potrzebuj kamer.
Nie potrzebuj aparatu.

Ty dostarczasz mi dane i materiay, kt贸rych wymagam do projektu.
Ja bior to i buduj film.

Nie o偶ywiam zdj jak tanie efekty.

sharedPost.text:
Lets talk about your part!

You will work it out for yourself, and whats more, youll do it right. If you have done all the work you say you have and if the part is within your range, you cannot fail. Work and patience never fail.

Notice everything around you  watch yourself cheerfully. Collect and save in your soul all the riches of life and the fullness of it. Keep those memories in order. You can never tell when you will need them, but they are your only friends and teachers in your craft. They are your only paints and brushes. And they will bring you reward. They are yours  your own property. They are not imitations and they will give you experience, precision, economy, and power.
- Richard Boleslavsky, Acting, The First Six Lessons

NEW DATES FOR JANUARY SCENE-STUDY CLASS 

THURSDAYS, 
January 8th, 15th, 22nd and 29th - 6-9 pm. ヰ

In this Scene-study class, in my bongo productions studio, were preparing and taping scenes, telling compelling stories, reviewing foundational process preparation techniques and analysis, with a focus on screen acting skills and technique, using 2 cameras.

Sign up now to revitalize your screen acting experience. 

Come train with actor and coach, Michael Caruana. Expert guidance and coaching, trusted, since 1996, at bongo productions. 

Comprehensive training with the three steps of our CERTIFICATE PROGRAM.

Private Coaching
Scene-study
Audition Technique

Professional coaching, with Michael Caruana, at bongo productions, trusted, since 1996! 

bongo productions is a proud member of AACE! (Association of Acting Coaches and Educators) 

www.bongoproductions.com

Weekly Wins!

Come on then, whats been your little victory this week? 

Maybe you landed an audition, nailed a self-tape, finally updated your headshots, or just made it through Monday without swearing at the universe.

Big or small, every win counts, drop yours in the comments and lets give each other a bit of well earned applause.

# **AKTORZY POSZUKIWANI | KRAKW **

**O projekcie:**

Do zajawkowego** non-profit** projektu szukamy aktor贸w!

Jest to projekt filmowc贸w z Krakowa, realizowany docelowo na konkurs Berlin Commercial Festival (kategoria Spec).

**Fabua: **

Akcja rozgrywa si w XVI-XVIII wieku, w  posiadoci brytyjskich arystokrat贸w, kt贸rzy podczas kolacji okazuj si wampirami. Degustacja tajemniczego trunku przeradza si w k贸tni. 

POSTACIE:

* *Wampir* - DIALOG W JZYKU ANGIELSKIM (British English), m偶czyzna 30-40 lat, klasyczna uroda. Jeden z arystokrat贸w na kolacji. Podczas degustacji podanego trunku zaczyna si mdrzy o smaku, wchodzc z innymi w k贸tni. 
* *Arystokrata* - DIALOG W JZYKU ANGIELSKIM (British English), m偶czyzna 30-40 lat, ostre rysy twarzy. K贸ci si z wampirem.  

* *Ofiara* - m偶czyzna 20-35 lat, pikne, klasyczne rysy.  Nieprzytomna ofiara jest g贸wn "dekoracj" na du偶ym stole w posiadoci wampir贸w. 

* *Suga* -  m偶czyzna, 25-35 lat. Podaje kieliszki arystokratom, epicko odkrywa g贸wne danie na stole. Scena zawiera upadek na ziemi (materac) - mile widziane osoby wysportowane lub z dowiadczeniem kaskaderskim.  

* *Dziewczyna* - kobieta 20- 30 lat. Ratuje swojego ukochanego, przebierajc si za sug, podaje wampirom wino.

**Szczeg贸y realizacji:**
- Jeden dzie zdjciowy w Krakowie, wstpnie planowany midzy 20-22 stycznia

- Z racji na typ projektu jestemy otwarci na wszelkich chtnych, od profesjonalnych aktor贸w po amator贸w 

- Postacie bd charakteryzowane w peruki i  makija偶 (informacja dla os贸b z alergiami) 
- Mimo braku bud偶etu produkcja ma charakter profesjonalny, czonkowie ekipy s osobami na co dzie pracujcymi w bran偶y filmowej, gwarantujemy du偶o funu i peen profesjonalizm:) 

**Kontakt:**

Osoby zainteresowane udziaem prosz o kontakt na maila: **kingakornak@gmail.com **

wraz z przesaniem informacji o sobie: zdjcia, wizyt贸wka (najchtniej w jzyku angielskim, szczeg贸lnie jeli to rola z tekstem), portfolio/showreel, wymiary, miasto zamieszkania.

items.text:
So many are staring at the fear around AI. We are looking at the proof that people still crave humans in a room. Broadways 20242025 season hit $1.89B with 14.7M attendances. Amazon MGM has publicly committed to ramping up theatrical releases (around 1214 films a year near-term), and Apple just scored its biggest theatrical opening to date with F1 ($144M global opening weekend).

Thats exactly why we built The Actors Copilot: to support the surge in independent filmmaking. Now more than ever, actors dont have to wait to be chosen  you can help create the work, build the credits, and tell the stories that matter.

The Actors Copilot uses AI in a positive way to cut prep time and overwhelm, so your choices stay rooted in your own truth  whether its a self-tape, a rehearsal room, or the early stages of getting a film off the ground.

And were not claiming to have all the answers. Were simply doing our part too  Our 2026 Film Retreat, is designed to help actors step into making festival-ready work together, with real mentorship, real collaboration, and real ownership.                Download the free PDF and follow for launch updates.   https://the-actors-copilot.mykajabi.com/the-actors-copilot

Setgefl眉ster 4: "Darsteller Seele, nutzt Du Schmerz als Rolle?" 

In diesem Teil wird deutlich, warum Setgefl眉ster mehr ist als ein Blick hinter die Kulissen. Wir sprechen nicht nur 眉ber Drehtage, Abl盲ufe und typische Set-Momente, sondern 眉ber das, was Darsteller wirklich mitbringen, ihren inneren Kern. Denn auch wenn jemand vor der Kamera souver盲n wirkt, bedeutet das nicht, dass innen alles leicht ist. 

Der Einstieg f眉hlt sich erst nach lockerer Pause an, kurze Begr眉ung, ein bisschen Set-Alltag, dieses Gef眉hl von, wir reden einfach. Und dann kippt es in eine Situation, die viele kennen, aber kaum jemand anspricht: Narben werden sichtbar. 

Genau hier passiert etwas Wichtiges: Wir zeigen, wie man N盲he nicht durch Schweigen baut, sondern durch Haltung. Denn Respekt ist nicht, so zu tun als w盲re nichts da. Respekt ist, den Menschen zu sehen und die richtige Form zu finden. Im Gespr盲ch wird klar, dass es einen Unterschied gibt zwischen Starren und ehrlicher Neugier, zwischen Voyeurismus und Verbindung. 

Dann wird es konkret, weil wir nicht nur 眉ber Narben als Symbol sprechen, sondern 眉ber Narben als medizinisches Thema. Es f盲llt der Begriff Keloidnarben, dazu hypertrophe Narben, und sogar die Info, dass es unterschiedliche Auspr盲gungen geben kann. 

Was Setgefl眉ster Teil 4 besonders macht, ist die n盲chste Ebene: Intimit盲t und Selbstwert. Wir sprechen dar眉ber, was es bedeutet, wenn man seinen K枚rper nicht einfach neutral erlebt, sondern als etwas, das bewertet wird. Da geht es um Licht, das man lieber ausmacht. 

Und hier kommt der Br眉ckenschlag zur Schauspielerei: Eine Rolle verlangt Pr盲senz. Pr盲senz bedeutet, Du bist da, mit K枚rper, Stimme, Blick, Atmung. 

Zu mir, Christian Weie 

Ich bin Christian Weie, Medienunternehmer, Content Creator und Inhaber der Karrideo Image- und Eventfilmproduktion aus K枚ln. Ich entwickle Bewegtbildformate, erz盲hle Geschichten f眉r Unternehmen,Organisationen und Pers枚nlichkeiten und kenne als Darsteller beide Seiten der Kamera. 

Wie w眉rdest Du wollen, dass man Dich auf etwas Sichtbares an Deinem K枚rper anspricht, damit es sich respektvoll anf眉hlt? 

Gef盲llt dir das Video, dann abonniere den Kanal, aktiviere die Glocke, gib dem Video einen Daumen nach oben, schreib Deine Sicht in die Kommentare und besuche mind_body_coach_ auf Instagram f眉r weitere Impulse. 

Christian Weie aka @christian_ugc_creator

items.text:
Hi everyone. This is future-facing, not an immediate ask.

Im a director developing my first feature. My first completed screenplay turned out to be the kind of project that, if Im fortunate, may represent a culmination rather than a starting point, so Im thinking long term and realistically.

The project is an independent, non-studio film. It is a deportation story set in Honduras and designed to be roughly three hours. Im fully aware this is not industry friendly or something a studio would buy, and that is intentional. This is a passion project I expect to finance independently if it ever happens.

Im not looking for script feedback.

What Im trying to do is educate myself years in advance.

For those of you who have worked on or around independent features, especially international or location-heavy productions, I would appreciate insight on practical difficulties you encountered, mistakes you wish you had planned for earlier, insurance or legal considerations I should be aware of, and logistical challenges that often get underestimated.

I am actively working on smaller and more practical projects to build toward this, but I want to understand the realities ahead of time so Im not na茂ve about what it takes.

Any experience-based advice is appreciated. Thank you for reading.

CASTING CALL  A PLACE NOT MINE (CABARET MUSICAL) 

Do you want to be part of something special next summer?

Are you looking for a creative project that helps you grow as a performer, collaborate with other artists, and build your portfolio?

Were casting for A Place Not Mine, an original cabaret musical inspired by real-life experiences of the writer, reimagined in a magical world influenced by shows like Wicked and contemporary musical theatre.

A story about belonging, identity, love, and finding your voice.

We are looking for London-based actors / actor-singers who are excited to collaborate and tell meaningful stories together.

 Roles available:

Riven 路 Seraphine 路 Mirra 路 Selene 路 Aurora 路 Oris 路 Vespera 路 Sylas 路 Rowan

 Please note:

The role of Riven includes emotional closeness and light intimacy with the main character (male). We are looking for performers who feel comfortable exploring this as part of the story.

 Project information:

This is an unpaid project, created as a development / showcase production, with the aim of presenting the work in a professional theatre setting.

The project will offer:

 Professional performance credit

 Showreel / recorded footage of the final performance

 A collaborative, supportive rehearsal process

 Availability:

Rehearsals expected to take place between March/April July, with performances planned for July/August. (exact dates TBC).

 How to audition:

Please send:

 CV

 Showreel or self-tape

 Two singing videos (one musical theatre song + one song of your choice)

to:  emilvasilev296@gmail.com, just add the name of the character you're applying for. 

(Feel free to reach out with any questions!)

If this feels like a project youd enjoy, wed truly love to hear from you

**CASTING CALL: THREE ACTOR-SINGERS FOR RECURRING MUSICAL COMEDY PROJECT **

**Project Title:** Standing On Shoulders 

**Production Company:** Independent 

**Casting Director:** Adam Scamvougeras 

**Union Status:** Non-Union 

**Compensation:** Credit & Footage Provided 

What if The Beatles were socially inept or The Monkees were morally corrupt? You get Standing On Shoulders! This project is an original musical comedy project that mixes narrative storytelling with humorous songs, performed by a recurring ensemble.

We are seeking three actor-singers to complete the four-person performance group.  

This particular project is acting-first. Actors should have strong comedic instincts and solid singing abilities. Instrumental ability is seen as a plus but not required. The music itself is created in collaboration with talented musicians from Vancouver and abroad.

While this project is ongoing, it is not a full-time commitment. Scheduling is flexible and performers will have plenty of time for other acting opportunities. This is a collaborative, passion-driven project designed to grow over time.

In 2026, we will be creating a few musical comedy videos. The long-term ambition with this project is to make albums or features starring the band. 

This is a recurring project for actors interested in returning to the same project over time. 

The available roles are as follows:

BAND MEMBER #1 (Male, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The suave one. His motivation for being part of the band is to meet girls. 

BAND MEMBER #2 (Male, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The punk one. His motivation for being part of the band is as a chance to rebel against the entertainment industry. 

BAND MEMBER #3 (Female, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The ambitious one. Her motivation for being part of the band is to get noticed. She sees the band as a stepping stone to better things and is always one foot out the door. 

For submissions, please submit a headshot, a resume (if available), and two short videos (30-60 seconds each): 

1) Singing sample

2) Acting sample for the role you're submitting for. It can be a brief monologue, a conversation with your friend, a self-written bit, etc. 

Please email to adamscamvougeras@gmail.com. Also, please include a brief message in the email explaining why you feel youre right for the project and what interests you about it. 

Thank you so much for taking the time to consider my project, and I** **wish you all the happiest of holidays.

Ich bin Operns盲ngerin (Sopran) mit langj盲hriger B眉hnenerfahrung und Gesangslehrerin. Neben einem umfangreichen Opern-, Operetten- und Konzertrepertoire biete ich sowohl Gesangsunterricht als auch musikalische Beitr盲ge f眉r festliche Anl盲sse und Galas an.

Gesangsunterricht:

Ich habe klassischen Gesang studiert und biete Online-Gesangsunterricht an, der individuell an Ihre M枚glichkeiten, Interessen und Ziele angepasst ist  in allen Stilrichtungen (Klassik, Musical, Pop, Rock). Mein Unterricht umfasst Einsing眉bungen zur Entwicklung Ihrer Stimme, verbesserte Atmungstechniken und das Einstudieren von Liedern Ihrer Wahl. Dabei erkl盲re und demonstriere ich viel, um meinen Sch眉lern die Inhalte verst盲ndlich zu machen. Der Unterricht findet bequem per Zoom oder WhatsApp statt. Gerne k枚nnen Sie bei einem kostenlosen Kennenlernen meine Unterrichtsmethoden ausprobieren.

Musikalische Beitr盲ge f眉r besondere Anl盲sse:

Ich bin auf der Suche nach neuen Wirkungsst盲tten und freue mich 眉ber Solo- und gemeinsame Auftritte mit anderen K眉nstlern. Ob Konzerte, Galas, Events oder festliche Anl盲sse  ich biete Ihnen eine vielseitige, musikalisch hochwertige Gestaltung, die Ihre Veranstaltung zu einem unvergesslichen Erlebnis macht.

Melden Sie sich gerne bei mir, um einen Termin f眉r den Gesangsunterricht oder die musikalische Gestaltung Ihrer Veranstaltung zu vereinbaren!

items.title: Hi! I'm an Italian dancer and I'm looking for a summer season job for this year!

items.text:
CASTING CALL  A PLACE NOT MINE (CABARET MUSICAL) 

Do you want to be part of something special next summer?

Are you looking for a creative project that helps you grow as a performer, collaborate with other artists, and build your portfolio?

Were casting for A Place Not Mine, an original cabaret musical inspired by real-life experiences of the writer, reimagined in a magical world influenced by shows like Wicked and contemporary musical theatre.

A story about belonging, identity, love, and finding your voice.

We are looking for London-based actors / actor-singers who are excited to collaborate and tell meaningful stories together.

 Roles available:

Riven 路 Seraphine 路 Mirra 路 Selene 路 Aurora 路 Oris 路 Vespera 路 Sylas 路 Rowan

 Please note:

The role of Riven includes emotional closeness and light intimacy with the main character (male). We are looking for performers who feel comfortable exploring this as part of the story.

 Project information:

This is an unpaid project, created as a development / showcase production, with the aim of presenting the work in a professional theatre setting.

The project will offer:

 Professional performance credit

 Showreel / recorded footage of the final performance

 A collaborative, supportive rehearsal process

 Availability:

Rehearsals expected to take place between March/April July, with performances planned for July/August. (exact dates TBC).

 How to audition:

Please send:

 CV

 Showreel or self-tape

 Two singing videos (one musical theatre song + one song of your choice)

to:  emilvasilev296@gmail.com, just add the name of the character you're applying for. 

(Feel free to reach out with any questions!)

If this feels like a project youd enjoy, wed truly love to hear from you <3

CASTING CALL  A PLACE NOT MINE (CABARET MUSICAL) 

Do you want to be part of something special next summer?

Are you looking for a creative project that helps you grow as a performer, collaborate with other artists, and build your portfolio?

Were casting for A Place Not Mine, an original cabaret musical inspired by real-life experiences of the writer, reimagined in a magical world influenced by shows like Wicked and contemporary musical theatre.

A story about belonging, identity, love, and finding your voice.

We are looking for London-based actors / actor-singers who are excited to collaborate and tell meaningful stories together.

 Roles available:

Riven 路 Seraphine 路 Mirra 路 Selene 路 Aurora 路 Oris 路 Vespera 路 Sylas 路 Rowan

 Please note:

The role of Riven includes emotional closeness and light intimacy with the main character (male). We are looking for performers who feel comfortable exploring this as part of the story.

 Project information:

This is an unpaid project, created as a development / showcase production, with the aim of presenting the work in a professional theatre setting.

The project will offer:

 Professional performance credit

 Showreel / recorded footage of the final performance

 A collaborative, supportive rehearsal process

 Availability:

Rehearsals expected to take place between March/April July, with performances planned for July/August. (exact dates TBC).

 How to audition:

Please send:

 CV

 Showreel or self-tape

 Two singing videos (one musical theatre song + one song of your choice)

to:  emilvasilev296@gmail.com, just add the name of the character you're applying for. 

(Feel free to reach out with any questions!)

Dieses Jahr haben wir etwas ver盲ndert.

 

Wir haben aufgeh枚rt, Schauspiel nur 眉ber Technik, Wissen und richtig machen zu denken.

 

Wir haben die Casting-Mastermind gestartet  mit elf Menschen, die bereit waren f眉r Pr盲senz statt Performance. Wir haben w枚chentlich gearbeitet, gefilmt, trainiert, Szenen gebaut, Energiearbeit gemacht und echte Ausstrahlung vor der Kamera entwickelt.

 

Viele von ihnen wurden in Schauspiel- und People-Agenturen aufgenommen, bekamen Rollen, Engagements oder Preise. Nicht weil sie fertig waren, sondern weil sie wirkten.

 

Im Oktober waren wir vier Tage lang in Irland. Showrealszenen, Embodiment, Natur, Workshops, Luxus, Stille, Tiefgang. Dort ist klar geworden: Technik reicht nicht. Pr盲senz entscheidet.

 

Damit entstand die Essenz-Methode.

 

Eine Methode aus Schauspiel, Nervensystem, Kamera, Energie und Embodiment  in 7 Buchstaben:

E  Erleben

S  Selbst

S  Seele

E  Emotion

N  N盲he

Z  Zwischen den Zeilen

 

2026 werden wir diese Methode weitergeben.

Erster Schritt: **Essenz-Workshop am 10. Januar.**

Live, on Camera, begrenzt, Einstieg in die weitere Zusammenarbeit.

Wenn du den Link m枚chtest, kommentiere **ESSENZ**.

items.text:
Setgefl眉ster 4: "Darsteller Seele, nutzt Du Schmerz als Rolle?" 

In diesem Teil wird deutlich, warum Setgefl眉ster mehr ist als ein Blick hinter die Kulissen. Wir sprechen nicht nur 眉ber Drehtage, Abl盲ufe und typische Set-Momente, sondern 眉ber das, was Darsteller wirklich mitbringen, ihren inneren Kern. Denn auch wenn jemand vor der Kamera souver盲n wirkt, bedeutet das nicht, dass innen alles leicht ist. 

Der Einstieg f眉hlt sich erst nach lockerer Pause an, kurze Begr眉ung, ein bisschen Set-Alltag, dieses Gef眉hl von, wir reden einfach. Und dann kippt es in eine Situation, die viele kennen, aber kaum jemand anspricht: Narben werden sichtbar. 

Genau hier passiert etwas Wichtiges: Wir zeigen, wie man N盲he nicht durch Schweigen baut, sondern durch Haltung. Denn Respekt ist nicht, so zu tun als w盲re nichts da. Respekt ist, den Menschen zu sehen und die richtige Form zu finden. Im Gespr盲ch wird klar, dass es einen Unterschied gibt zwischen Starren und ehrlicher Neugier, zwischen Voyeurismus und Verbindung. 

Dann wird es konkret, weil wir nicht nur 眉ber Narben als Symbol sprechen, sondern 眉ber Narben als medizinisches Thema. Es f盲llt der Begriff Keloidnarben, dazu hypertrophe Narben, und sogar die Info, dass es unterschiedliche Auspr盲gungen geben kann. 

Was Setgefl眉ster Teil 4 besonders macht, ist die n盲chste Ebene: Intimit盲t und Selbstwert. Wir sprechen dar眉ber, was es bedeutet, wenn man seinen K枚rper nicht einfach neutral erlebt, sondern als etwas, das bewertet wird. Da geht es um Licht, das man lieber ausmacht. 

Und hier kommt der Br眉ckenschlag zur Schauspielerei: Eine Rolle verlangt Pr盲senz. Pr盲senz bedeutet, Du bist da, mit K枚rper, Stimme, Blick, Atmung. 

Zu mir, Christian Weie 

Ich bin Christian Weie, Medienunternehmer, Content Creator und Inhaber der Karrideo Image- und Eventfilmproduktion aus K枚ln. Ich entwickle Bewegtbildformate, erz盲hle Geschichten f眉r Unternehmen,Organisationen und Pers枚nlichkeiten und kenne als Darsteller beide Seiten der Kamera. 

Wie w眉rdest Du wollen, dass man Dich auf etwas Sichtbares an Deinem K枚rper anspricht, damit es sich respektvoll anf眉hlt? 

Gef盲llt dir das Video, dann abonniere den Kanal, aktiviere die Glocke, gib dem Video einen Daumen nach oben, schreib Deine Sicht in die Kommentare und besuche mind_body_coach_ auf Instagram f眉r weitere Impulse. 

Christian Weie aka @christian_ugc_creator 
 
#setgefluester #filmset #acting #schauspiel

sharedPost.text:
CASTING CALL 
Mr Poole (and The Father)
 in "Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde"
Grove Productions

Were seeking an actor to join our touring production as Mr Poole, Dr Jekylls long-serving butler, who witnesses his masters terrifying descent. This is a key supporting role with strong emotional scenes. The role also includes a small secondary part, The Father.

 Blind casting  all actors welcome
ｏ Working-class / regional accent required

 Pay
 拢101 per performance (inc. holiday pay)
 拢15 per hour for rehearsals (inc. holiday pay)

锔 Mid-run replacement  fast learning essential
 Small rep company  cast help move props/set & assist with get-outs
 Reasonable adjustments available

 Auditions: 9 January
 Rehearsals: 15 & 16 January

锔 Performance Dates:
 19 Jan  Clevedon School (Bristol)
 3 Feb  The Crypt (Gloucester)
 9/10 Feb (TBC)  Hodge Hill (Birmingham)
 9 March  Blakehay Theatre, Weston-super-Mare
 12 March  Blakehay Theatre, Weston-super-Mare
 16 March  Cheltenham Ladies College

 To apply:
Send your CV + video audition (using the provided Poole extract) to
admin@groveproductions.org
Closing date for application: 5pm 6th January

Poole Extract

Context - Poole has become increasingly concerned about his master, Dr Jekyll, and has gone to Jekylls friend, Utterson, for help. In this scene, Poole has just asked Utterson to listen at the door to his masters voice, as Poole believes it is not his master but a different man, or monster.

Poole:
Well, Mr Utterson, you are a hard man to satisfy. But Ill do it yet. All this last week, he or it or whatever it is that lives in the laboratory, has been crying night and day for some sort of medicine and cannot get it to his mind. It was sometimes his way  the masters that is  to write his orders on a sheet of paper and throw it on the stair. Weve had nothing else this week back. Nothing but papers, and a closed door, and the very meals left there to be smuggled in when nobody was looking. Well sir, every day, ay, and twice and thrice in the same day, there have been orders and complaints, and I have been sent flying to all the wholesale chemists in town. Every time I brought the stuff back, there would be another paper telling me to return it, because it was not pure, and another order to a different firm. This drug is wanted bitter bad, sir, whatever for.

DM for more info

items.text:
We are seeking strong, talented comedic actors for our production of 'YOU CAN'T TAKE IT WITH YOU'. These are non-equity auditions by appointment. All roles are volunteer. No housing or pay will be provided. 

AUDITION DATES:  
- Monday, February 2nd, 6:00pm-10:00pm
- Tuesday, February 3rd, 6:00pm-10:00pm
*Auditions will consist of monologues and cold reading.

LOCATION: Delray Beach Playhouse (Delray Beach, FL) 

PREPARATION: 
-Please prepare a short comedic monologue.
-Actors may also be asked to do cold reads (sides will be provided).

In lieu of attending in-person auditions, VIDEO SUBMISSIONS WILL BE ACCEPTED  Deadline for submission is January 29 at 9:00pm. 

VIDEO PREPARATION:
- Please slate your name and confirm your location.
- please tape a 1-minute comedic monologue.
*Due by 9pm, Jan. 29th

Full Audition Breakdown here: [https://auditionsmanager.com/registration.php?AU=v10HYL1698](https://auditionsmanager.com/registration.php?AU=v10HYL1698)

www.chansons.show

Award-winning singer Stefanie Rummel takes the audience on a captivating musical journey  from the caf茅s of Paris to the cabaret stages of Berlin and the clubs of Manhattan.
With songs in the style of Piaf, Weill, Sondheim, as well as her own compositions, she tells stories of lifes special moments  full of longing, humor, warmth, and depth.
Celebrated as heart-touching and praised for her brilliant stage presence, she enchants audiences in the USA, the UK, and across Europe  and will return to Australia on tour next year.

 Outstanding voice  TheReviewHub
 A revelation  LondonTheatre1
An inspiring, moving musical cabaret about life  shaped by songs, personality, and storytelling.

Bernhard Lehner accompanies masterfully on piano.
Seven songs are written by Stefanie Rummel (lyrics & music). These songs were produced in collaboration with Tom Schl眉ter (pianist & music producer).

An evening full of emotion, humor, and international flair.

#stefanierrummel1 #insititutrummel #singer 
#songsfromlife  #ChansonsShow @EstillVoiceTraining @AdlFringe  @NewcastleFringe @GallusTheater

Dieses Jahr haben wir etwas ver盲ndert.

 

Wir haben aufgeh枚rt, Schauspiel nur 眉ber Technik, Wissen und richtig machen zu denken.

 

Wir haben die Casting-Mastermind gestartet  mit elf Menschen, die bereit waren f眉r Pr盲senz statt Performance. Wir haben w枚chentlich gearbeitet, gefilmt, trainiert, Szenen gebaut, Energiearbeit gemacht und echte Ausstrahlung vor der Kamera entwickelt.

 

Viele von ihnen wurden in Schauspiel- und People-Agenturen aufgenommen, bekamen Rollen, Engagements oder Preise. Nicht weil sie fertig waren, sondern weil sie wirkten.

 

Im Oktober waren wir vier Tage lang in Irland. Showrealszenen, Embodiment, Natur, Workshops, Luxus, Stille, Tiefgang. Dort ist klar geworden: Technik reicht nicht. Pr盲senz entscheidet.

 

Damit entstand die Essenz-Methode.

 

Eine Methode aus Schauspiel, Nervensystem, Kamera, Energie und Embodiment  in 7 Buchstaben:

E  Erleben

S  Selbst

S  Seele

E  Emotion

N  N盲he

Z  Zwischen den Zeilen

 

2026 werden wir diese Methode weitergeben.

Live, on Camera, begrenzt, Einstieg in die weitere Zusammenarbeit.

items.text:
*CALL FOR CROWD PARTICIPANTS (EXTRAS) // UNPAID*

*Berlin, SO36, 04.01.2026*

For our student short film project _Signal One_ we are looking for people to be part of the *background crowd* in a punk club scene, shot at *SO36 Berlin* around noon on *January 4th, 2026* .

What the movie is about: _After meeting face-to-face with the punk scene in 1977s West Berlin, a Yugoslav philosophy student has to learn how to confront and accept the person he really is._

We are looking for around 50 people who want to go wild in a *70s punk club scene* and are happy to dress accordingly. All ages and all genders welcome!

Unfortunately, the project is unpaid but we will provide snacks on set. Estimated shooting time: *approx. 3-4 hours* , starting around noon.

If youre interested or want more information, feel free to text me by phone or send an email to signalone.casting@posteo.de. 

Looking forward to hearing from you :)

--- 

*German Version:*

F眉r unser studentisches Kurzfilmprojekt Signal One suchen wir Leute, die *Teil der Crowd* (Kompars*innen) in einer *Punkclub-Szene* sein m枚chten. Die Szene wird am 04.01.2026 gegen Mittag im *SO36 Berlin* gedreht.

Worum es im Film geht:

_Nachdem er der Punk-Szene im West-Berlin von 1977 begegnet ist, muss ein jugoslawischer Philosophiestudent lernen, sich seiner eigenen Identit盲t zu stellen und diese zu akzeptieren._

Wir suchen ca. 50 Personen, die Lust haben, in einer *70er-Punkclub-Szene* die Partyg盲ste zu spielen und sich passend zu kleiden. Alle Altersgruppen und Geschlechter willkommen!

Das Projekt ist unbezahlt, aber es wird Snacks am Set geben.

Gesch盲tzte Drehzeit: *ca. 34 Stunden* , ab Mittag.

Wenn du interessiert bist oder mehr Informationen haben m枚chtest, melde dich gern direkt unter dieser Nummer oder E-Mail an signalone.casting@posteo.de

Wir freuen uns auf eure Nachrichten! :)

items.text:
Hallo und gesundes neues Jahr euch! 

F眉r ein kleines Filmprojekt, welches ich mit ein paar Freunden auf die Beine stellen wollte, suche ich seit einiger Zeit eine Laien-Darstellerin (ich hatte hier schonmal inseriert, vor einiger Zeit).  Rolle: Eine eiskalte Auftragskillerin.

Da wir das Drehbuch zusammen erstellen wollten, w盲r es sch枚n , wenn du auch wirklich "intrinsischen" Spa daran h盲ttest, in so eine Rolle zu schl眉pfen.

Also, um es direkt zu sagen: Ein bisschen kranke Psychogedanken sollten mit im Spiel sein  und ein bisschen Faible f眉r Waffen w盲r auch nicht schlecht, aber  unter den klassischen Schauspielstudentinnen ist sowas leider nicht so oft zu finden.

Handlung des Films: Eine Auftragskillerin erwischt einen Privatdetektiv in ihrem Haus beim Durchsuchen ihrer Sachen. Sie stellt ihn zur Rede, fragt ihn ausf眉hrlich aus und -entgegen dem sonst 眉blichen Krimi-Klischee der "Rettung in letzter Sekunde" - exekutiert ihn. D眉ster. Realistisch. Eiskalt.

Drehort soll entweder Berlin oder Bayreuth sein, mit meiner kleinen Pen&Paper-Rollenspielgruppe im April. Aber auch, wenn du von weiter weg kommst: Hilfe am Drehbuch oder eigene Ideen einbringen geht immer.

Hey everyone  Im looking to hire someone locally to help finish setting up a home content-creation studio in Fort Worth (76116).

I already have all the gear, I just need help connecting and configuring everything so it works smoothly.

What I need help with:

  Lighting setup

  USB webcam (EMEET)

  Shure microphone + audio interface

  Elgato Stream Deck (sound effects)

  Testing everything in StreamYard

This is not a class or training, just a hands-on setup job. Should take about 12 hours.

If you have experience with:

  Podcast setups

  Streaming / YouTube / content creation

  Audio & video gear

please comment or DM me. Paid gig. Thanks!

items.text:
Project: Bax P.I. Bite Size - Bax Meets Bonnie

Production company: ShoreHouse

Production type: Short/Mini Series

Role: Bonnie

Role type: lead (female, 20s-30s)

Project Rate: $200 flat rate (10 hrs. Single day shoot)

Union status: non union

Location: Monticello, FL

Key requirements: talent will be interacting with live animal (mini schnauzer)

For consideration, submit headshots to: hey@sammijay.com 

Key production dates:

Apply by Jan. 4; self-tapes due Jan. 7; decisions or call backs by Jan. 9. Wardrobe fitting Jan. 17; shoots Jan. 25 in Monticello, FL. Travel coverage does not include air travel, hiring for local and/or drivable only. We are open to shifting the shooting and fitting dates to work with talent availability.

About Bax P.I.: Imagine if Sin City and the Muppets had a baby thats Bax P.I. Its a world of mystery, crime, comedy, and friendship. When were in Baxters world, theres very few human characters, one exception being Bonnie. When schnauzer detective Bax Dillinger meets the beautiful and mysterious Bonnie, were asked to question the reality of a small dog. To Bax, Bonnie is the most beautiful woman hes ever seen, and in reality shes his favorite chew bone.  This is part of a mini series to promote the feature length project set to go into production later in 2026.

Bonnies look: tall, slender physique. Minimum 5 5. Angular face. Extravagantly and elegantly fashioned. Red carpet level. Wears all white. Diversity encouraged.

Bonnies personality: mysterious, like she knows something we arent cool enough to know about. Edgy and witty. Intoxicatingly charming. A sophisticated flirt 

References: Carmen San Diego, Halle Berry, Debbie Harry, Uma Thurman

Well, Mr Utterson, you are a hard man to satisfy. But Ill do it yet. Nothing but papers, and a closed door, and the very meals left there to be smuggled in when nobody was looking. Well sir, every day, ay, and twice and thrice in the same day, there have been orders and complaints, and I have been sent flying to all the wholesale chemists in town. This drug is wanted bitter bad, sir, whatever for.

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonat贸w **Grupa1940** poszukuje  kobiety w wieku 20  25 do roli modej asystentki niemieckiej pani archeolog. Szukamy osoby bez permanentnych brwi czy farbowanych wos贸w, bez kolczyk贸w na twarzy. Posta bdzie mie kwestie po niemiecku. Mile widziana osoba z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrza czy Katowic. Wystpi w kilku odcinkach. Zdjcia pr贸bne realizujemy  w Gliwicach. Spotykamy si w wybrane niedziele z wyprzedzeniem 2 3 tygodniowym.  

 

**Na wiosn roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjc do tego **projektu. Bdziemy realizowa mini serial oparty o wtki grupy okultystycznej **Ahnenerbe** kt贸ra chce zdoby synne artefakty ale w tym kto im chce przeszkadza. items.text:
This is a question for all sag union people out there. Originally our feature film untethered we wanted make a sag film but after talking to my EP he recommended that we book a sag E actress and currently we are talking to on.

My question is under sag aftra rules what are the requirements for sag Eligible contracts, when it comes down to payment and per day?

topComments.text: Tyler Schacht in other words, if you hire a sag eligible actor, there are no contract rules for you to abide by. Only if they are Sag members already. Sag eligible means the actor has enough taft Hartley credits to apply to sag but have not applied yet...they are still nonunion. Whomever you hire, you can check to see if thry are sag or nonunion simply by calling the sag office and checking them thoroughly. The office can tell you, the casting director, if they are registered sag members or not.

Hi Tyler. SAG-AFTRA Actor and signatory producer here. Youre getting some incomplete answers. Basically it comes down to whether or not you decided to make your project under a SAG-AFTRA contract or not.  And pay requirements depend on the type of SAG-AFTRA contract you decided to use for your project. It has nothing to do with the union eligibility of one of the actors. 

Most of the people on this thread are correct about the SAG eligible Actor. SAG eligible means they are still non-union. They are eligible to join the union, but have not yet done so. So if your project is not being made under a SAG-AFTRA contract, they are still allowed to work your project, and there are no considerations you have to worry about in regard to the union. However, no SAG-AFTRA MEMBER actors may work on your nonunion project. 

This is where a lot of your answers are incomplete. If you did your project in a SAG-AFTRA contract, depending on the type of contract, you may or may not have to pay your actors at all. Even if they are SAG-AFTRA members. However, doing your project under a SAG contract will allow SAG-AFTRA members to act in your project. Contracts like SAG micro budget, SAG student, SAG Indie, and SAG ultra low budget all have ways of allowing for ultra low budget projects to do things like defer pay or no pay for actors. Even if they are full members of the union. But if you make your project a SAG-AFTRA contract project, then ALL actors in the project are covered and protected by SAG-AFTRA rules. This means that if you had budgeted a pay rate for actors, then all actors whether they are union members or not, would be subject to the same pay scale. Whether that is no pay, $150 a day, or $1000 a day. SAG-AFTRA contracts are not about treating some actors better than others. They are about making sure that all actors are protected, treated fairly, and paid fairly and most important transparently.

So if I am understanding correctly, you have a non-union project, that has employed a SAG-AFTRA eligible Actor. In this case, you have absolutely no requirements regarding the union. This is because your project is not being made under a SAG-AFTRA agreement.  the rules are about your project status. Not about the Actors eligibility status.

The Ghost That Could- Casting Call/Updates

Grateful the project was recently awarded the: @fromtheheartproductions Hot Film In The Making Roy W. Dean Grant FALL 2025 laurel

Excited to be moving into the test shoots stage of production in coming months(Jan-April). I went ahead and emailed some self tape request to those who expressed serious interest via email-

To anyone who responded before who is still interested in being part of the team/actor email: mattiemacaya@gmail.com with a resume and area of skill, attach resume

For self tapes please follow below instructions: 

For this stage, we would love to see a short, silent self-tape that gives us a sense of your emotional range and presence. No monologue is needed. 

Please submit this by NO LATER then end of dayJanuary 17 2026. For anyone interested in production assisting/marketing/makeup/etc email NO LATER then end of day January 20 2026.

What to include:

* Film either inside or outside  whatever feels most comfortable and natural to you
* Keep the framing horizontal
* A simple moment where you move through an emotion or emotional shift (this can be very subtle)30seconds to 1 minute. 
* Please include a brief slate at the end with your name

After the slate, please answer the following two questions on camera (casually  no need to overthink):

1. When do you feel most like yourself?
2. Whats something you notice about people that others often miss?



Shoot Details: 

Test Shoot for Film Short

Non-union

Shoot Dates: TBD January - April 2026

Rate of Pay: Food/Beverage provided

Location: Denver, CO and surrounding locations

Side note from the  : if youre submitting note the team will not respond to direct PMs on here nor will anyone chase you down for follow up if you are selected- that is ON YOU. Meet the self tape/application deadline if youre serious and can commit, there can only be ONE ghost on this project everyone else will have to haunt elsewhere.

Thank you all for continued interest and support! Lets collaborate on some magical storytelling in the new year and get this on 2026-2027 Festival Circuit.

items.text:
**Film Editor | Drama  Short Films  Feature Fiction** 

Hi everyone,
Im **Jean Apa**, a film editor based in **Sweden**, with experience across many areas of cinema and a strong focus on editing and storytelling in recent years.

I recently received the **Best Editor award at Torino Film Festival** for the feature film *Suicide Tuesday.* My credits include **2 feature fiction films** and **15+ short films**, mostly drama-driven projects.

I speak **several languages** and enjoy working with international teams. Im comfortable **working remotely or traveling**, depending on the project. Budgets can vary, and Im always happy to start a conversation when the project and vision feel right.

Feel free to message me and tell me about your project.

Cheers

Jean Apa
